    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Patterns tooled onto the spine of a leather-bound book, consisting of a fillet, usually double, running from head-to tail alongside the joint, with horizontal lines intersecting it at intervals.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
